// Iota Draconis - god-pvp-s15 (god-pvp)
//notes: best *obtainable* high impact as of end-of-season S15
//this is going to sound like ass, but running liquid coils is not always terrible. liquid + high impact with no charge mw will almost always get the 3-bolt kill (~199 dmg) with no activation requirement, giving you a LOT more consistency. if you have a charge time mw or don't have high impact, go for the fastest charge time and pray you can get the 4-bolt.
//
//recommended mw: charge time (range if liquid coils) tags:god-pvp
dimwishlist:item=3044460004&perks=3250034553,1687452232,1645158859,2213355989

// Glacioclasm - god-pvp-s15 (god-pvp)
//notes: best not-entirely-unobtainable high impact as of end of season 15
//in S16, high impacts are getting a damage bump, so
//
//SEASON 15
//this is going to sound like ass, but running liquid coils is not always terrible. liquid + high impact with no charge mw will almost always get the 3-bolt kill (~199 dmg) with no activation requirement, giving you a LOT more consistency. if you have a charge time mw or don't have high impact, go for the fastest charge time and pray you can get the 4-bolt.
//
//SEASON 16
//you can now 3 bolt 6 resilience or lower with accelerated + charge time mw + high impact, 8 res or lower with either (not both) accelerated or charge time
//so that's just better
//
//S15 recommended mw: charge time or range
//S16 recommended mw: charge time tags:god-pvp

// Bottom Dollar - god-pvp (god-pvp)
//notes: not sure why everyone just forgot about bottom dollar, but imo it's still top 5 for energy hand cannons and top 10 for hand cannons in general. oh right, it's because it comes from gambit (other than that pretty good one xur sold a while ago). this is a sniper hand cannon - before the 120 nerfs, it outranged pulses, and it can still hang today. unfortunately, high impact no longer gives free 2 taps, but you can still get 1c2b kills on low resilience guardians in the second half of the mag. of course, it has a miniscule mag, so that could be challenging to work around, but you can just treat it as a passive bonus - at that point, though, you may as well just have a damage perk. mkclip gets you the 2 tap on guardians 2 res or less, while rampage will always just get you a 1c2b.

// Bottom Dollar - pvp (pvp)
//notes: not sure why everyone just forgot about bottom dollar, but imo it's still top 5 for energy hand cannons and top 10 for hand cannons in general. oh right, it's because it comes from gambit (other than that pretty good one xur sold a while ago). this is a sniper hand cannon - before the 120 nerfs, it outranged pulses, and it can still hang today. unfortunately, high impact no longer gives free 2 taps, but you can still get 1c2b kills on low resilience guardians in the second half of the mag. of course, it has a miniscule mag, so that could be challenging to work around, but you can just treat it as a passive bonus - at that point, though, you may as well just have a damage perk. mkclip gets you the 2 tap on guardians 2 res or less, while rampage will always just get you a 1c2b.

// Royal Entry - god-pve (god-pve)
//notes: purely in terms of burst, clown cartridge rockets are the highest dps option in the game (up to, like, 5 rockets). for total damage, explosive light has *slightly* higher dps than lasting impression, but that changes with wolfpack rounds. the perk appears to scale off of the rocket's blast damage, which is dramatically increased by lasting impression - something unavailable on ascendancy. it also has intrinsic tracking, putting it ahead of other lasting impression rockets. with one person on gjallarhorn, or with clown cartridge for burst, royal entry is the best rocket in the game.
//recommended mw: reload tags:god-pve

// Royal Entry - pve (pve)
//notes: purely in terms of burst, clown cartridge rockets are the highest dps option in the game (up to, like, 5 rockets). for total damage, explosive light has *slightly* higher dps than lasting impression, but that changes with wolfpack rounds. the perk appears to scale off of the rocket's blast damage, which is dramatically increased by lasting impression - something unavailable on ascendancy. it also has intrinsic tracking, putting it ahead of other lasting impression rockets. with one person on gjallarhorn, or with clown cartridge for burst, royal entry is the best rocket in the game.

// Tarantula - god-pve (god-pve)
//notes: nowhere near the best linear, but surprisingly not as terrible as you may think. box breathing is only cancelled when you fire before the 1s timer, not when you pull the trigger: as such, with some skillful timing, it can proc while you're charging for decent dps and really high total damage (box breathing is a *33% BUFF*). you'll want to run liquid coils and forego the charge time mw, as you'll be waiting 1s between each shot regardless. combine with field prep for extra reserves and even more total damage. tarantula may not kill things *fast,* but while other linears may fall just short, it will *definitely* kill things... eventually.
//recommended mw: reload tags:god-pve
dimwishlist:item=3335343363&perks=1840239774,1687452232,2869569095,2551157718

// Tarantula - pve (pve)
//notes: nowhere near the best linear, but surprisingly not as terrible as you may think. box breathing is only cancelled when you fire before the 1s timer, not when you pull the trigger: as such, with some skillful timing, it can proc while you're charging for decent dps and really high total damage (box breathing is a *33% BUFF*). you'll want to run liquid coils and forego the charge time mw, as you'll be waiting 1s between each shot regardless. combine with field prep for extra reserves and even more total damage. tarantula may not kill things *fast,* but while other linears may fall just short, it will *definitely* kill things... eventually.
//recommended mw: reload tags:pve

// Frozen Orbit - god-pvp (god-pvp)
//notes: there isn't a best sniper in any slot (other than whisper). what determines the value of a sniper is how it feels to each specific user: if you prefer the feel of aachen to beloved, you're going to perform better with aachen. with that said, looking at potential alone, frozen orbit is pretty likely to be your favorite. aggressive frames are a very popular pick because of the potential for easy clean ups and super shutdowns, and frozen orbit is the stat and perk monster of the agg frames. top tier options for all sniping playstyles: you can go for the classic handling + aim assist combo with something like firmly planted + snapshot, sit your ass down and lane with no distractions + opening shot, get reported for cheating with double aim assist perks like firmly planted + opening shot, or use your AWP to body shot people with kill clip or empowering rift + high impact. if snapshot were in the left column, frozen orbit would ruin crucible more than beloved or revoker ever did.
//recommended mw: handling or range tags:god-pvp

// The Third Axiom - god-pvp (god-pvp)
//notes: there was a time when everybody was saying this pulse is better than messenger. while thankfully that craze died down, third axiom is definitely still a good option, if constrained by its frame. adaptives have the slowest ttk of the pulse archetypes at .93s, but they're the most forgiving, requiring only 5c2b. as such, they have always shined in consistency - all adaptives feel *great* for some reason, and you don't need to be as accurate to achieve the optimal ttk (you can still 3 burst guardians 5 res or lower with only *one* headshot, and 2c7b will kill anyone). third axiom is no exception with its excellent stats and scope, and for some players (particularly on controller), it *might* be a better overall option than something like a messenger that requires more accuracy. either mkclip x1 or rampage x1 will allow you to 3 burst with all body shots, while mkclip x2 will 5c0b anybody and rampage x2 will 5c1b all resiliences or 4c2b most. elemental capacitor gives you the potential to hit 100 in any of the affected stats pretty easily.
//recommended mw: range tags:god-pvp

// The Third Axiom - pvp (pvp)
//notes: there was a time when everybody was saying this pulse is better than messenger. while thankfully that craze died down, third axiom is definitely still a good option, if constrained by its frame. adaptives have the slowest ttk of the pulse archetypes at .93s, but they're the most forgiving, requiring only 5c2b. as such, they have always shined in consistency - all adaptives feel *great* for some reason, and you don't need to be as accurate to achieve the optimal ttk (you can still 3 burst guardians 5 res or lower with only *one* headshot, and 2c7b will kill anyone). third axiom is no exception with its excellent stats and scope, and for some players (particularly on controller), it *might* be a better overall option than something like a messenger that requires more accuracy.

// Farewell - god-pvp (god-pvp)
//notes: lightweight sidearms are incredibly slept on. the most forgiving archetype with a 3c2b requirement, the 2nd fastest ttk at .67s, and the mobility bonus as a cherry on top. farewell is pretty much as good as lightweights get - you've got barrels for better stats, almost all desirable perks in the right column, and a choice between rangefinder for top-tier sidearm range or other consistency perks to make this thing aim for you. it should be noted that the difference between a max range roll and a base range roll is only about 3 meters, so while you can totally spec into range to make full use of the space around you, it's not strictly necessary. don't dismiss frenzy on a sidearm or smg for 6s - you're going to be moving around so much and getting into so many engagements that you can expect to have it up a reasonable amount of the time.
//recommended mw: range or handling tags:god-pvp

// Sojourner's Tale - god-pvp (god-pvp)
//notes: sojourner's tale is pretty much as good as it gets for legendary energy slugs, with excellent stats all around, classic top tier perks, and some interesting rolls, too. can't go wrong with quickdraw + opening shot, though I would try threat detector - it's a toss up whether you'll be in range with a slug, but the constant bonus rather than quickdraw's on-draw effect will feel nice. tunnel vision is interesting because this is really the only special it will work on in pvp, since you have to reload one shot at a time (which also makes it easier to proc). killing wind seems intriguing for a legendary chaperone roll, but you can't exceed 100 range, so you would have to spec all into handling for it to have a noticeable effect (which isn't necessarily a bad thing).
//recommended mw: range or handling tags:god-pvp

// Exile's Curse (Adept) - god-pvp-s15 (god-pvp)
//notes: best non-sunset high impact as of end of season 15
//in S16, high impacts are getting a damage bump, so
//
//SEASON 15
//this is going to sound like ass, but running liquid coils is not always terrible. liquid + high impact with no charge mw will almost always get the 3-bolt kill (~199 dmg) with no activation requirement, giving you a LOT more consistency. if you have a charge time mw or don't have high impact, go for the fastest charge time and pray you can get the 4-bolt.
//
//SEASON 16
//you can now 3 bolt 6 resilience or lower with accelerated + charge time mw + high impact, 8 res or lower with either (not both) accelerated or charge time
//so that's just better
//
//S15 recommended mw: charge time or range
//S16 recommended mw: charge time tags:god-pvp

// Exile's Curse (Adept) - god-pvp-s16 (god-pvp)
//notes: best non-sunset high impact as of end of season 15
//in S16, high impacts are getting a damage bump, so
//
//SEASON 15
//this is going to sound like ass, but running liquid coils is not always terrible. liquid + high impact with no charge mw will almost always get the 3-bolt kill (~199 dmg) with no activation requirement, giving you a LOT more consistency. if you have a charge time mw or don't have high impact, go for the fastest charge time and pray you can get the 4-bolt.
//
//SEASON 16
//you can now 3 bolt 6 resilience or lower with accelerated + charge time mw + high impact, 8 res or lower with either (not both) accelerated or charge time
//so that's just better
//
//S15 recommended mw: charge time or range
//S16 recommended mw: charge time tags:god-pvp

// Exile's Curse - god-pvp-s15 (god-pvp)
//notes: best non-sunset high impact as of end of season 15
//in S16, high impacts are getting a damage bump, so
//
//SEASON 15
//this is going to sound like ass, but running liquid coils is not always terrible. liquid + high impact with no charge mw will almost always get the 3-bolt kill (~199 dmg) with no activation requirement, giving you a LOT more consistency. if you have a charge time mw or don't have high impact, go for the fastest charge time and pray you can get the 4-bolt.
//
//SEASON 16
//you can now 3 bolt 6 resilience or lower with accelerated + charge time mw + high impact, 8 res or lower with either (not both) accelerated or charge time
//so that's just better
//
//S15 recommended mw: charge time or range
//S16 recommended mw: charge time tags:god-pvp

//
//SEASON 15
//this is going to sound like ass, but running liquid coils is not always terrible. liquid + high impact with no charge mw will almost always get the 3-bolt kill (~199 dmg) with no activation requirement, giving you a LOT more consistency. if you have a charge time mw or don't have high impact, go for the fastest charge time and pray you can get the 4-bolt.
//
//SEASON 16
//you can now 3 bolt 6 resilience or lower with accelerated + charge time mw + high impact, 8 res or lower with either (not both) accelerated or charge time
//so that's just better
//
//S15 recommended mw: charge time or range
